Ethics and Anti-Corruption Comission (EACC) detectives have arrested a former senior officer of the Kilifi County Government and two businesspeople over an irregular tender award and illegal acquisition of public property. Dr Timothy Malingi, the former Chief Officer of Health Services, was arrested alongside the directors of Skywards Agencies Ltd -- Cornell Otieno Mark and his wife Jackline Atieno Olewe. The three are expected to face several charges over irregular award of a tender concerning the construction of a dispensary block and a pit latrine at Vishakani in Kaloleni Ward, and illegal acquisition of public property. More follows..  